Iavan Pijoos, News24A pregnant lady was also shot during the protest in Eldorado Park. (Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; A pregnant woman was shot in the stomach with rubber bullets by police after violence erupted in Eldorado Park, south of Johannesburg on Monday afternoon.Eldorado Park Community Policing Forum member, Denzil Blignaut told News24 on Monday evening that the woman was standing in her yard when police allegedly opened fire.He said an elderly man was reportedly also hit in the face with a rubber bullet.&ldquo;The streets are an absolute nightmare. We are struggling to get people medical attention, because ambulances can&rsquo;t enter the area,&rdquo; Blignaut said.He said the roads were still blocked with burning tyres.Protests broke out in the area on Monday morning and parts of the N12 and Golden Highway were barricaded with rocks and burning tyres.Several vehicles were pelted with rocks and a truck was set alight.JMPD spokesperson Wayne Minnaar said on Monday evening eight people were arrested but only seven got charged, while one was released.Minnaar said the Golden Highway would remain closed.Blignaut said the CPF would meet on Monday evening to discuss a way forward. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.